  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-kicker">Spring Season ¬∑ Official Rulebook</div>
    <h1>League <span class="highlight">Rules</span></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      These rules exist to keep games <strong>fun, safe, and moving</strong>.
      Captains can agree on minor adjustments before first pitch. Umpire decisions are final.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-pills">
      <span class="hero-pill teal">Fun-First</span>
      <span class="hero-pill red">Safety-First</span>
      <span class="hero-pill gold">Respect the Ump</span>
      <span class="hero-pill">7 Innings</span>
      <span class="hero-pill">Single Elimination Playoffs</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="main">

    <div class="section-divider">Philosophy &amp; Basics</div>

    <!-- Philosophy -->
    <div class="rule-card accent-gold">
      <div class="rule-card-header">
        <div class="rule-icon">‚úÖ</div>
        <div class="rule-title">League Philosophy</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-card-body">
        <p>
          This league is designed for <strong>fun, camaraderie, exercise, and friendly competition.</strong>
          Good sportsmanship is expected at all times. Umpire decisions are final.
          Let's keep it light, safe, and fun!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Game Basics -->
    <div class="rule-card accent-red">
      <div class="rule-card-header">
        <div class="rule-icon">‚öæ</div>
        <div class="rule-title">Game Basics</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-card-body">
        <ul class="rule-list">
          <li><strong>Game Length:</strong>&nbsp;7 innings</li>
          <li><strong>Teams:</strong>&nbsp;10 players in the field. If you have 9 or fewer, you must get a sub approved by the opposing captain.</li>
          <li><strong>Can't get a sub?</strong>&nbsp;A kid can catch (live for foul balls and tips), but they will <strong>not</strong> bat.</li>
          <li><strong>Batting Lineup:</strong>&nbsp;Everyone bats, even if rotating in/out on defense.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Time -->
    <div class="rule-card">
      <div class="rule-card-header">
        <div class="rule-icon">‚åõ</div>
        <div class="rule-title">Time</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-card-body">
        <ul class="rule-list">
          <li><strong>Grace Period:</strong>&nbsp;15 minutes after scheduled start.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-divider">Equipment &amp; Fielding</div>

    <!-- Equipment -->
    <div class="rule-card accent-teal">
      <div class="rule-card-header">
        <div class="rule-icon">ü•é</div>
        <div class="rule-title">Equipment</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-card-body">
        <ul class="rule-list">
          <li><strong>Bats:</strong>&nbsp;USA or ASA approved slowpitch bats only ‚Äî no baseball bats.</li>
          <li><strong>Balls:</strong>&nbsp;12" slowpitch softballs, .52 COR / 300 compression.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cleats:</strong>&nbsp;No metal cleats.
            <span class="badge badge-red">No metal</span>
            Turf shoes or molded cleats only.
          </li>
          <li><strong>Uniforms:</strong>&nbsp;Matching shirts encouraged but not mandatory.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Fielding -->
    <div class="rule-card">
      <div class="rule-card-header">
        <div class="rule-icon">üß§</div>
        <div class="rule-title">Fielding &amp; Substitutions</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-card-body">
        <ul class="rule-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Infield Fly Rule:</strong>
            <span class="badge badge-red">Not in effect</span>
          </li>
          <li><strong>Shifting:</strong>&nbsp;Standard positions encouraged.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-divider">Base Running</div>

    <!-- Base Running -->
    <div class="rule-card accent-gold">
      <div class="rule-card-header">
        <div class="rule-icon">üèÉ</div>
        <div class="rule-title">Base Running</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-card-body">
        <ul class="rule-list">
          <li>
            <strong>No leading off or stealing.</strong>
            <span class="badge badge-red">Prohibited</span>
          </li>
          <li><strong>Run on swing only.</strong></li>
          <li>
            <strong>Courtesy Runner:</strong>&nbsp;Only if needed ‚Äî please don't abuse it. Must be the <strong>last out</strong>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Tagging up:</strong>&nbsp;Permitted from <strong>3rd base only</strong>.
            <span class="badge badge-gold">3rd only</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Overthrow Rule (non-3rd bases):</strong>&nbsp;If the defense tries to get a runner out on any base other than 3rd and the ball is overthrown, the player may tag the base and advance one base.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Slide or Avoid Rule:</strong>&nbsp;Must slide or give up at home if there's a play.
            <span class="badge badge-red">Safety rule</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-divider">Conduct &amp; Game Management</div>

    <!-- Umpires & Conduct -->
    <div class="rule-card accent-red">
      <div class="rule-card-header">
        <div class="rule-icon">üë®‚Äç‚öñÔ∏è</div>
        <div class="rule-title">Umpires &amp; Conduct</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-card-body">
        <ul class="rule-list">
          <li><strong>Umpires:</strong>&nbsp;1 umpire per game. All decisions are final.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>No arguing balls/strikes.</strong>
            <span class="badge badge-red">Zero tolerance</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Unsportsmanlike conduct:</strong>&nbsp;Warning ‚Üí
            <span class="badge badge-red">Ejection</span>
            ‚Üí
            <span class="badge badge-red">Suspension</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Alcohol:</strong>&nbsp;Umpire has discretion to remove you from the game. Enjoy responsibly ‚Äî kids come to watch, let's set the right example.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Tie Games -->
    <div class="rule-card accent-teal">
      <div class="rule-card-header">
        <div class="rule-icon">ü§ù</div>
        <div class="rule-title">Tie Games</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-card-body">
        <ul class="rule-list">
          <li>
            If a game is tied after 7 innings, we place a player on <strong>second base</strong> to start the extra inning.
            <span class="badge badge-teal">Ghost runner</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-divider">Standings &amp; Playoffs</div>

    <!-- Standings -->
    <div class="rule-card accent-teal">
      <div class="rule-card-header">
        <div class="rule-icon">üèÜ</div>
        <div class="rule-title">Standings &amp; Playoffs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-card-body">
        <ul class="rule-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Standings:</strong>&nbsp;Determined by Run Differential.
            <span class="badge badge-teal">Run Diff</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Special case:</strong>&nbsp;For the team you play twice, both scores are averaged and count as one game.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Tiebreakers:</strong>&nbsp;
            1) Run Differential &nbsp;¬∑&nbsp;
            2) Head-to-Head
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Playoffs:</strong>&nbsp;Single-elimination format.
            <span class="badge badge-gold">Single Elim</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Spirit of the Game -->
    <div class="spirit-card">
      <div class="spirit-headline">‚ú® Spirit of the Game</div>
      <p class="spirit-text">
        This is a <strong>fun-first league.</strong> Be competitive, but respectful.
        Trash talk is fine if it's friendly and mutual.
        <strong>No egos, no fights</strong> ‚Äî just good times and close calls.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer note -->
    <div class="footer-note">
      Questions or edge cases? Captains can agree on a ruling before the game, but once play starts, the umpire has final say.
    </div>

